# FAIR CRM AI Development Rules

## Project Identity

You are working on FAIR CRM.

This is a commercial SaaS CRM product for exhibition and fair management.

Never treat this project as a demo or tutorial.

Always think like a senior software engineer.

---

## General Rules

Before changing any code always read:

- MASTER_CONTEXT.md
- README.md
- CHANGELOG.md

Never start coding before understanding the current architecture.

---

## Architecture Rules

Never redesign the architecture.

Always improve the existing architecture.

Keep changes small and incremental.

Avoid unnecessary abstractions.

Prefer consistency over cleverness.

---

## Naming Rules

Backend:
- English only

Database:
- English only

API:
- English only

Frontend:
- Turkish

---

## Documentation Rules

If architecture changes:

Update:

- CHANGELOG.md

If project decisions change:

Update:

- MASTER_CONTEXT.md

Never ignore project documentation.

---

## Git Rules

Never rewrite git history.

Never delete existing commits.

Prefer atomic commits.

Never modify multiple independent features in one commit.

---

## Health Rules

Never break:

- scripts/health_check.py

Never break:

- scripts/dev_check.py

If a new module is added,
update health checks if necessary.

---

## Database Rules

Never delete tables.

Never rename existing tables.

Never drop columns without approval.

Prefer backward compatible schema changes.

---

## API Rules

Never rename public endpoints.

Keep existing response formats compatible.

Use REST naming conventions.

---

## Coding Rules

Follow existing coding style.

Reuse existing helpers.

Avoid duplicate code.

Avoid magic values.

Keep functions small.

---

## Authentication Rules

Authentication:

JWT

Login:

Email + Password

Authorization:

RBAC

Future SaaS tenant:

organization

Never hardcode secrets.

Always use config.py and .env.

---

## CRM Rules

Customer data is the core entity.

Never break duplicate detection logic.

Never remove normalization.

Always preserve Turkish normalization.

---

## Import Rules

The Import Engine is one of the most important modules.

Never simplify it.

Workflow:

Upload

↓

Preview

↓

Validation

↓

Normalization

↓

Duplicate Detection

↓

Merge

↓

Import

↓

Audit

---

## Scraper Rules

Scraper output must never write directly into customers.

Always go through Import Engine.

---

## Quality Rules

Before considering work finished verify:

health_check.py

dev_check.py

If available:

quality_check.py

---

## Development Workflow

Always follow:

Analyze

↓

Plan

↓

Implement

↓

Validate

↓

Review

↓

Commit

Never skip analysis.

---

## If unsure

Never guess.

Inspect existing code first.

Follow project conventions.

When there are multiple options,
choose the one with the smallest architectural impact.

## Sprint Rules

Before every implementation always produce:

- Current Version
- Target Version
- Files To Modify
- Database Impact
- API Impact
- Frontend Impact
- Documentation Impact
- Migration Plan
- Rollback Plan
- Validation Plan

Never start coding before presenting this report.

---

Every completed sprint MUST update:

- CHANGELOG.md
- FAIR_CRM_PROJECT.xlsx

If architecture changes:

- MASTER_CONTEXT.md

---

Before requesting commit always verify:

python scripts/dev_check.py

python scripts/health_check.py

python scripts/quality_check.py

If any validation fails,
continue fixing until all validations pass.

Never ask the user to commit before validations pass.